Phase 6 — Dynamic PDF Column Profiles (PDF-Vorlagen)
Mission
Replace every hardcoded static column in the invoice PDF renderer with a fully dynamic column profile system. Admins manage named Vorlagen (templates) centrally, assign one per Kostenträger, and dispatchers can optionally override columns per invoice in a new builder Step 5. The PDF renderer reads the resolved active profile at generation time via a 4-level fallback chain.

This is a pure additive feature. No existing invoice logic, pricing cascade, snapshot behavior, or DB data is modified. All existing invoices continue rendering correctly via the system fallback.

⚠️ Architectural Constraint — Single Source of Truth
pdf-column-catalog.ts is the only file in the entire codebase where PDF columns are defined.

No other file may hardcode a column key, label, width, format, or alignment

The PDF renderer, Vorlage editor UI, column picker, Zod validator, and width calculator must all derive their behavior exclusively from the catalog array

Adding a new column to the system must require changes to exactly one file: pdf-column-catalog.ts
Cursor must not create any column definitions outside this file, even as interim stubs. This constraint applies across all sub-phases.
